{"symbol": "ATXN7L3", "uniprot": "Q14CW9", "protein_name": "Ataxin-7-like protein 3", "length": 347, "function": "Component of the transcription regulatory histone acetylation (HAT) complex SAGA, a multiprotein complex that activates transcription by remodeling chromatin and mediating histone acetylation and deubiquitination. Within the SAGA complex, participates in a subcomplex that specifically deubiquitinates both histones H2A and H2B (PubMed:18206972, PubMed:21746879). The SAGA complex is recruited to specific gene promoters by activators such as MYC, where it is required for transcription. Required for nuclear receptor-mediated transactivation. Within the complex, it is required to recruit USP22 and ENY2 into the SAGA complex (PubMed:18206972). Regulates H2B monoubiquitination (H2Bub1) levels. Affects subcellular distribution of ENY2, USP22 and ATXN7L3B (PubMed:27601583)", "ensembl_gene": "ENSG00000087152", "scores": {"selectivity": 0.1613, "protein_drug": 0.296, "rna_drug": 0.57}, "flags": {"surface": true, "enzyme": false, "mod_aso": true, "mod_sirna": false}, "details": {"nominated_modality": "ASO", "winning_axis": "RNA", "quadrant": "RNA-preferred", "best_route": "antibody/biologic", "sm_score": "0.35", "sirna_score": "0.241", "aso_score": "0.474"}, "modality": "ASO", "structure": "data/structures/ATXN7L3.pdb", "pockets": [{"rank": 1, "druggability": 0.255, "volume": 227.0, "residues": [342, 343, 344, 345, 346]}, {"rank": 2, "druggability": 0.084, "volume": 343.3, "residues": [115, 118, 119, 122, 123]}, {"rank": 3, "druggability": 0.022, "volume": 271.7, "residues": [171, 172, 173]}], "links": [{"key": "uniprot", "label": "UniProt", "url": "https://www.uniprot.org/uniprotkb/Q14CW9"}, {"key": "alphafold", "label": "AlphaFold", "url": "https://alphafold.ebi.ac.uk/entry/Q14CW9"}, {"key": "opentargets", "label": "Open Targets", "url": "https://platform.opentargets.org/target/ENSG00000087152"}, {"key": "genecards", "label": "GeneCards", "url": "https://www.genec